  "riddle": "1. Unearth a charming venue where cinematic dreams unfold beneath vaulted ceilings in Santa Barbara. How many guests can this theater accommodate?\n\n2. There's a style that embraces Spanish influence and is named for its historic churches—what languages can its essence be expressed in?\n\n3. In a coastal California town, a holy place was established long ago. When did this landmark open its doors to the devoted?\n\n4. An ancient fortress overlooking the sea bears a notable title. In what year did it secure its status as a historical landmark in California?\n\n5. Ascend above sea level to find this fort’s resting place. What height, in meters, welcomes visitors at its highest point?\n\n6. Seek the collective commendation the public gives to this historic site. How many stars does it earn in traveler evaluations?\n\n7. Calculate the elevation backdrop and user rating from previous clues. What is the absolute difference between these two values?\n\n8. Return to point of interest as you gaze upon the same historic fort and uncover its elevation once more. What is the height that greets you?\n\n9. Journey to an edifice where ornate design tells tales of community governance. What architectural style defines this landmark's character?\n\n10. As you ponder, consider the name of this courthouse. How many vowels are found within its title?\n\n11. A place steeped in nostalgia, this theater once graced with grandeur boasts a minimum number of seats. What is its recorded capacity?\n\n12. Stroll through a thoroughfare known for bustling life; what multitude of languages can be encountered here at the outset of the text?\n\n13. Adventure awaits as you explore the vicinity of a once-prominent airline. How many hotels can you discover nearby its historical mention?\n\n14. Reflect on the previous number of nearby lodgings you found. How many distinct divisors can be attributed to that figure?\n\n15. In a final reckoning, combine the elevation from clues 5 and 8, the seat count from clue 11, and the divisors from clue 14. Compute the result of (elevation + elevation + seats + divisors) modulo 10. What single digit emerges from this summation?",
